<para> <image type="html" name="twoheads-detail.png"></image>
   Le-Jeng Andy Shiue Subdivision methods recursively refine a control mesh and generate points approximating the limit surface. This package consists of four popular subdivision methods and their refinement hosts. Supported subdivision methods include Catmull-Clark, Loop, Doo-Sabin and <formula id="0">$ \sqrt{3}$</formula> subdivisions. Their respective refinement hosts are Pqq, Ptq, Dqq and <formula id="0">$ \sqrt{3}$</formula> refinements. Variations of those methods can be easily extended by substituting the geometry computation of the refinement host. <linebreak/>
